title: Cal trying to do something it hasn't done since 1951
text:
Cal trying to do something it hasn't done since 1951 FOXSports 17 hrs ago © Gary A. Vasquez-USA TODAY Sports October 12, 2013; Pasadena, CA, USA; California Golden Bears quarterback Jared Goff (16) throws a pass against the UCLA Bruins during the first half at the Rose Bowl. Mandatory Credit: Gary A. Vasquez-USA TODAY Sports Cal hasn't been an inept program over the course of its history. In fact, the program has been very competitive and has produced incredible NFL talents, such as Packers QB Aaron Rodgers.
AdChoices However, when Cal takes on Utah on Saturday in Salt Lake City, the Bears will be trying to do something they haven't done since 1951.
Cal is seeking its first road win over an AP top-5 opponent since 1951 (at No. 3 Stanford) & 1st 6-0 start since 1950 & went to Rose Bowl.
— Ted Miller (@TedMillerRK) October 8, 2015 The Bears are also trying to start 6-0 for the first time since 1950. Needless to say, there's a lot on the line for Cal on Saturday.
